{"id":"3752","name":"Move Calendars II","tagline":"Duplicate events from one calendar to another","icon":"ios13 c4282601983 g59655","latest":"11727","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><b>The purpose of the shortcut is to duplicate events from one calendar to another (nothing deleted). </b> </p>\n<p>An example of usage is to move events from work calendar to shared familly calendar in order to share end-of-the day constraints.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><b>Steps </b> </p>\n<ul>\n\n<p></p><li>Let you decide the horizon to duplicate (1day, 1 week or 1 month)</li><p></p>\n<p></p><li>Detect the list of calendars that exist on your device (the list is created automatically but the constraint is that the calendars must have at least one event on the coming 30 days) and let you choose the origin calendar and the destination calendar to move events from/to </li><p></p>\n<p></p><li>Build the list of events to clone and let you choose the one you don't want to duplicate (by default everything is copied) </li><p></p>\n<p></p><li>Copy from one calendar to another avoiding duplicates (based on starting time and name) </li>\n</ul><p></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><b> Inspiration: </b></p>\n<p>This is an improved version of the \"move calendar\" shortcut shared by Matthew Cassinelli. https://www.matthewcassinelli.com/siri-shortcuts/</p>\n<p>Thank you Matthew for this idea.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><b> Limitations: </b></p>\n<p>Due to action limitations, does not include any type of repeats, event attendees, or the alter times.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><b> Possible improvements: </b> \n</p><ul>\n<li>2 way synchronization between the chosen calendars</li>\n<li>Remove event from destination calendar if it has been removed from the origin's since the last sync. (adding a note to created events to detect the origin of creation)</li>\n </ul><p></p>\n<p><br>\n<b> Thanks you: </b></p>\n<p>Thanks for telling me what you think about this shortcut.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - Oct. 21, 2019, 2:54 p.m.</strong></p>"}